Zygophylax convallaria
is a deep-sea species, having been reported largely from bathyal bottoms. As apparent from present material, however, it also ranges upwards into the lower neritic zone. The known bathymetric range on this coast is from 139 m ( Fewkes, 1881a ) to 748 m (
Henry et al . 2008
). Geographically, it has been reported in the western Atlantic from North Carolina (
Henry et al . 2008
) to the southern Caribbean Sea ( Fewkes 1881a ). Although recorded from the Pacific Ocean as well (e.g., Hirohito 1995 ; Stepanjants 2013 ), confirmation of its occurrence there seems warranted.

Reported distribution. Gulf coast of Florida.
Off the Florida Reef, 152 ftm ( 278 m ) ( Allman 1877: 12 , as
Lafoea convallaria
).— SW Florida shelf, outer shelf NW of Dry Tortugas , 25°33’N , 84°21’W , 101 ftm ( 185 m ) ( Clarke 1879: 243 , as
Lafoea convallaria
).

